cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for automatic detection and counting of insect pests in images taken inside field traps. This involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which are typically covered under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of deep learning models for pest detection also falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of parallel hardware for real-time performance, which could be related to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning models for pest detection could also be related to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
